Mind of literature
Written by Liu Xie, translated by Zhengqian Cheng

Chapter 1  Origin of Dao
The purpose of words is so magnificent as if  born like heaven and earth
seperated from chaos. Sun and moon shine alternatively with highest worth,
while moutains and rivers display their beauty passage in logic and reasons,
which is the verse for Dao that govens motion of stars and change of seasons.
When I see the rising of sun or the running of mounts, the high and low are ordered
so do the genesis of heaven and earth. And only man can be counted as the third,
where the nature and intelligence are focused.  We call them three arts,







